%N A256080 Non-palindromic balanced numbers in base 16.
%C A256080 Here a number is called balanced if the sum of digits weighted by their arithmetic distance from the "center" is zero. Palindromes (A029730) are trivially balanced, therefore they are excluded here.
%C A256080 This is the hexadecimal variant of the decimal version A256075 invented by Eric Angelini. See there, and the base-2 version A256082, for further information and examples.See A256090 for the primes in this sequence.
%o A256080 (PARI) is(n,b=16,d=digits(n,b),o=(#d+1)/2)=!(vector(#d,i,i-o)*d~)&&d!=Vecrev(d)
